<p id="Par43">Zhao et al. (
 <xref ref-type="bibr" rid="CR132">2015</xref>) proposed a 2D graphical representation method on the basis of nucleotide triplets (codons), as opposed to individual bases, in the DNA coding sequence strand. There are 64 codons including the 3 termination codons. Let 
 <italic>S</italic> = 
 <italic>s</italic>
 <sub>1</sub>
 <italic>s</italic>
 <sub>2</sub>…
 <italic>s</italic>
 <sub>
  <italic>n</italic>
 </sub> represent a random DNA sequence. On the basis of standard genetic codes, each codon in the sequence can be defined with the aid of a mapping 
 <italic>ɸ</italic>:
